summary:
The Security Council, having considered the report of the Secretary-General on the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force, 
1. Calls upon the parties concerned to implement immediately its resolution 338 (1973) of 22 October 1973; 
2. Welcomes the efforts of the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force to implement the Secretary-Generalâ€™s zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse, requests the Secretary-General to continue to take all necessary action and keep the Security Council informed, and urges troop-contributing countries to take preventive and disciplinary action; 
3. Decides to renew the mandate of the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force for a period of six months, until 31 December 2008; 
4. Requests the Secretary-General to submit, at the end of this period, a report on developments and measures taken to implement resolution 338 (1973).
